^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Okay, let's discuss the bidding a bit more. For the very reason that it happened, I like to play that a cue bid, particularly at the three level promises four trumps. That way, you follow the law of total tricks. Although Dee has 11 HCPs, she really has a pretty bad hand. The Jack of diamonds is likely to be worthless and she has lots of other Queens and Jacks. Believe it or not, I would be content to bid 2H with her hand. It is barely possible we miss a game, but not likely. It is more likely, as happened, if I cue bid, we will be down in 3.|
