^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Tough hand to play with the spade break, but lets see how we might plan. Once the club finesse wins, you can count two clubs and a heart for sure. And, if spades break 3-2, four spade tricks. That is seven tricks. You need two more. Probably the best line is to lead diamonds from dummy twice, hoping that Elizabeth has at least one diamond honor. In that case, one diamond ruff plus one diamond honor will get you to 9 tricks. SO, I would have led a diamond at trick two. However, with the bad spade break, it is likely you will lose two spades and two diamonds and a heart and be down one anyway. Regardless, I still think planning the hand makes sense.|
