^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Now as to the bidding. Over 1S, I have a slight preference for 1N rather than 2S, but either could be right. It is true diamonds are a worry in NT and the spades are not bad.  2S is certainly reasonable. I tend to like to have the A, K, or Q with only 3 card support, but it is not an essential requirement. With a singleton diamond, for example, instead of a doubleton, 2S is a very good bid and even with the hand as is, many experts would bid 2S.|
