^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|In an uncontested bidding, 2NT in that particular auction means 11-12 points and no four-card major and it is not forcing. 3NT in 1D-P-3NT auction promises 13-15 points and no four-card major. Over an overcall, there is no change to the meaning of those bids, except you should have a stopper in the bid suit. Further, to bid 2C you need at least five clubs and 10 plus points. My main point here is responder is the captain of the hand. That means you are responsible for making sure you get to game when you have a game forcing hand. On this hand, you have an opener and you must make some forcing bid below game, or bid game. So let me give an undo.|
